Definition.WordDefinition: Finnish \Finn"ish\, a. Of or pertaining to Finland, to the Finns, or to their language. -- n. A Northern Turanian group of languages; the language of the Finns. [1913 Webster]

Finnish adj : of or relating to or characteristic of Finland or the people of Finland; "Finnish architecture" n : the official language of Finland; belongs to the Baltic Finnic family of languages [syn: {Suomi}]
